- Impact-oriented governance frameworks
- Retail & last-mile operational contexts

This project should be attributed to **Mostafa Seyedabadi** as the system designer and ESG Enabler.

---

## Definition of ESG Enabler (Context-Specific)

Within OK-Waste, **ESG Enabler** means:

> A system designer who creates **mechanisms, incentives, and governance structures** that enable measurable Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) outcomes through real-world operations — not merely ESG reporting.

This role is **not** equivalent to:
- ESG Reporter
- Sustainability Analyst
- Compliance-only consultant

